---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Statement"
  description="Cookie statement for Results You Can Measure, explaining how cookies and similar technologies may be used on this website."
>
  <section class="page-hero legal-hero">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Cookies</p>
      <h1>Cookie statement.</h1>
      <p>What cookies and similar technologies are, how this site uses them and how to manage your preferences.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="section article-body legal-page">
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 27 May 2026</p>

    <h2>What cookies are</h2>
    <p>Cookies are small files placed on your device when you visit a website. Similar technologies, such as tracking pixels, local storage, scripts and device identifiers, can also store information on your device or access information from it.</p>

    <h2>How we currently use cookies</h2>
    <p>This website is a static Astro site. We do not set advertising, remarketing or behavioural tracking cookies. We do not embed third-party form widgets, chat tools, video players, pixels or social embeds that drop cookies in your browser. If we add any of these in future we will update this statement and ask for your consent before they load.</p>
    <p>The site does use a small amount of essential technical storage — for example a localStorage entry to remember your cookie banner choice itself, and Cloudflare bot-protection cookies set by our hosting layer. These are exempt under PECR Article 5(3) and do not require opt-in consent.</p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <p>We self-host the DM Sans web font, so normal font loading does not require a request to Google Fonts.</p>
    <p>Our contact form is handled by our own in-house form service hosted on Cloudflare in the UK at <code>forms.resultsyoucanmeasure.com</code>. It does not drop cookies in your browser; it accepts the form submission and routes it to us by email. Form data is held for 12 months and then deleted unless we are actively in conversation with you about the work.</p>

    <h2>Types of cookies we may use</h2>
    <h3>Strictly necessary cookies</h3>
    <p>These help the website work, keep it secure, remember privacy choices or deliver a service you have requested. They are not used for advertising.</p>

    <h3>Analytics or performance cookies</h3>
    <p>These help us understand how people use the site, which pages are useful and where the experience can be improved. We will only use non-essential analytics cookies where the correct consent process is in place.</p>

    <h3>Marketing cookies and pixels</h3>
    <p>These may be used to measure campaigns, build audiences or show relevant advertising. We will not use these without an appropriate consent mechanism.</p>

    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <p>You can control your preferences for any non-essential cookies through the cookie banner on this site. Click <a href="#" data-open-cookie-prefs>Manage cookies</a> at any time (also linked in the footer) to change your mind.</p>
    <p>You can also control cookies through your browser settings. You can block or delete cookies, although some essential website functions may not work as expected if you block all storage.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have a question about cookies on this site, email <a href="mailto:hello@resultsyoucanmeasure.com">hello@resultsyoucanmeasure.com</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
